				<h1 class="shead-style text-center">UTTAR PRADESH</h1>
				<p>It is true that without Uttar Pradesh there is no India. A part that signifies India for thousands of years is the heart of modern day India. Inhabited by human civilization for thousands of years, Uttar Pradesh has seen it all. A place with rich history, culture and influence has been ruled formidable empires for many years. As result of prolonged exposure to imperialism, culture and diversity it is a place that shows it all.</p><p>
                Home to many of the famous monuments, temples, holy shrines, mosques, churches that make it even more worthy of the jewel it is. As a centre of influence by many rulers, cultures, religion it is truly a place that has bestowed it s culture proudly over the years. Some of the best known monuments of Uttar Pradesh include Taj Mahal , Fatehpur Sikri, Bara Imambara, Varanasi Ghats. These places attract thousands of visitors every year. Home to many cultures Uttar Pradesh is home to many exquisite and unique cuisines, this makes it even more worthy of visiting. Varying from vegetarian dishes to non vegetarian items and from simple ordinary items to extraordinary Nawabiby items it is place the never fails to impress.
                </p>
